        "title": "fix: close readline interface and destroy read stream in transcript store",
        "body": "Related: #98467\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes file descriptor leak: `createReadStream` + `readline.createInterface` not cleaned up after `for await` loop.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nWrap loop in `try/finally` that calls `lines.close()` and `stream.destroy()`.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo user-visible change. Prevents file descriptor exhaustion.\n\n## Evidence\n\nRuntime verification (fix/readline-stream-leak, rebased on upstream/main 6495358f):\n\n```\ntranscripts-tool.test.ts — Test Files 1 passed, Tests 10 passed\n✓ transcripts tool > creates the core transcripts tool\n✓ transcripts tool > imports a speaker transcript and writes summary artifacts\n✓ transcripts tool > aborts pending auto-starts when the service stops\n... (10/10 ✓, Duration 4.10s)\n```\n\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard. Stream close+destroy verified.",
